    "body": "### Problem\n\n`langmap` works as expected for neovim motions etc but it quickly becomes _unusable_ when trying to use custom `maps` since those expect their assigned  `lhs` key , that as it seems isnt affected by the `langmap` setting.\r\n```lua\r\nvim.opt.langmap = {\r\n    \"ŒëA\", \"ŒíB\", \"Œ®C\", \"ŒîD\", \"ŒïE\", \"Œ¶F\", \"ŒìG\", \"ŒóH\", \"ŒôI\", \"ŒûJ\", \"ŒöK\", \"ŒõL\", \"ŒúM\", \"ŒùN\",\r\n    \"ŒüO\", \"Œ†P\", \"QQ\", \"Œ°R\", \"Œ£S\", \"Œ§T\", \"ŒòU\", \"Œ©V\", \"WW\", \"ŒßX\", \"Œ•Y\", \"ŒñZ\",\r\n    \"Œ±a\", \"Œ≤b\", \"œàc\", \"Œ¥d\", \"Œµe\", \"œÜf\", \"Œ≥g\", \"Œ∑h\", \"Œπi\", \"Œæj\", \"Œ∫k\", \"Œªl\", \"Œºm\", \"ŒΩn\",\r\n    \"Œøo\", \"œÄp\", \"qq\", \"œÅr\", \"œÉs\", \"œÑt\", \"Œ∏u\", \"œâv\", \"œÇw\", \"œáx\", \"œÖy\", \"Œ∂z\",\r\n}\r\nvim.keymap.set('n', 'Z', function() vim.notify(\"real lua function\") end,{noremap=true})\r\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nI would expect that all aspects of neovim respect the langmap thus making using different languages as input seamless.\r\n\r\n* Maybe have a way to set keymaps via keycodes (Below greek alpha and latin a have the same code on the keyboard )\r\n![image](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/assets/61395246/c26539d5-81af-4459-9dd7-a550ffbfcf1e)\r\n* Or extend the `langmap` to affect keymaps as well",
